SIMPLE: infelicity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infelicity
<hw>In`fe*lic"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Infelicities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>infelicitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inf⟦eacute⟧licit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Felicity</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being infelicitous;
unhappiness; misery; wretchedness; misfortune; lack of suitableness or
appropriateness.</def> <rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whatever is the ignorance and <qex>infelicity</qex> of the present
state, we were made wise and happy.</q>
<rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That (as an act, word, expression, etc.) which is
infelicitous; <as>as, <ex>infelicities</ex> of speech</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infelonious</ent>⟦br⟧
